s ago. If the Nahmads are <i>asking</i>
only 5.5 percent more for a painting they acquired with an irrevocable bid,=
 the market for high-value works must be pretty tough. <br/><br/>A last-min=
ute snafu prevented me from getting on a plane to Miami on Tuesday morning,=
 but this hiccup gave me the benefit of having time to talk to a slew of de=
alers, collectors, and advisors to get a true measure of this year=E2=80=99=
s shows. And given the distractions of attending=E2=80=94the traffic<i> and=
