r/><br/>It takes a lot of this kind of buying to really register in the mar=
ket. For those of us paying close attention, though, this has been the stor=
y of the last two years. The top of the market has gone quiet, as Nahmad kn=
ows, but the low end remains quite strong. (The middle of the market, howev=
er, is upside down; we=E2=80=99ll get to that shortly.) We can see this in =
auction data,
and economist <b>Clare McAndrew </b>reinforced that notion this autumn in h=
er report for Art Basel on collectors and gallery sales. <br/></td>
